EN.title: Arbitrary File Reading
EN.description: Arbitrary Files Reading is a vulnerability that allows an attacker to obtain arbitrary files contents on a remote server. This may include sensitive data, application source code, configuration files, etc. We recommend you to use regular expressions in access control checks.

EN.title: Log Forging
EN.description: An application does not sufficiently validate user input that allows an attacker to create a specially malformed item for a log file or inject malware into it.

EN.title: Error-code setting
EN.description: The setting defines HTTP status code that make a receiver to redirect users to a certain URL. So, the setting configures error pages for different HTTP status codes. The recommended range of values if 400-414, 500, 502-504.

EN.title: Vulnerable component jquery 2.0.1 (CVE-2019-11358)
EN.description: jQuery before 3.4.0, as used in Drupal, Backdrop CMS, and other products, mishandles jQuery.extend(true, {}, ...) because of Object.prototype pollution. If an unsanitized source object contained an enumerable __proto__ property, it could extend the native Object.prototype.

RU.title: jquery 2.0.1 (CVE-2019-11358)
RU.description: jQuery before 3.4.0, as used in Drupal, Backdrop CMS, and other products, mishandles jQuery.extend(true, {}, ...) because of Object.prototype pollution. If an unsanitized source object contained an enumerable __proto__ property, it could extend the native Object.prototype.

EN.title: Cross-Site Scripting
EN.description: The application does not sufficiently validate user input that allows attackers to to execute arbitrary code in the context of victim's browser bypassing the Same Origin Policy (SOP).

EN.title: Missing Encryption of Sensitive Data
EN.description: The software does not encrypt sensitive or critical information before storage or transmission.

EN.title: System Information Leak
EN.description: Debug pages or messages, error descriptions, stack tracing, etc. in productive systems allows attackers to obtain information about application internals that is useful for conducting attacks.

EN.title: Vulnerable component jquery 2.0.1 (CVE-2020-11023)
EN.description: In jQuery versions greater than or equal to 1.0.3 and before 3.5.0, passing HTML containing <option> elements from untrusted sources - even after sanitizing it - to one of jQuery's DOM manipulation methods (i.e. .html(), .append(), and others) may execute untrusted code. This problem is patched in jQuery 3.5.0.

RU.title: jquery 2.0.1 (CVE-2020-11023)

This problem is patched in jQuery 3.5.0.

EN.title: Secure setting in web.xml
EN.description: The setting defines secure flag for Set-Cookie HTTP header that defines if cookie are sent via secure connections only (https).

EN.title: Tracking-mode setting
EN.description: The setting defines if a session ID (JSESSIONID) is sent as a URL parameter or is stored in user Cookie.

EN.title: Hardcoded Password
